# Territory Developer — Project Overview

Unity 2D city-builder with isometric view. Players build and manage a city by placing roads, zones (residential/commercial/industrial), buildings, and managing economy.

## Language
All code, comments, XML docs, annotations, Debug.Log messages, and repository content must be in **English**.

## Stack
- Unity + C#, all game logic in MonoBehaviour classes
- Most files use `Territory.*` namespaces (partial migration; a few legacy files may remain in the global namespace)
- No dependency injection — managers reference each other via Inspector fields + `FindObjectOfType<T>()` fallback in Awake/Start

## Folder Structure (`Assets/Scripts/`)
- `Managers/GameManagers/` (94 files) — core game logic: grid, terrain, zones, roads, economy, simulation, helpers
- `Managers/UnitManagers/` (64 files) — data models: Cell, Zone, Building, Forest, HeightMap, CellData, WaterMap, etc.
- `Controllers/GameControllers/` (6 files) — CameraController, CityStatsUIController, etc.
- `Controllers/UnitControllers/` (38 files) — UI buttons, popups, sliders
- `Utilities/` (6 files) — DebugHelper, RoadPathCostConstants, etc.

## Key Architectural Facts
- **GridManager** is the central hub (~2070 lines, 13 direct dependencies). All cell operations go through it. Decomposition: **TECH-01** in `BACKLOG.md`.
- **Only singleton**: `GameNotificationManager.Instance` (with DontDestroyOnLoad)
- **Data models**: MonoBehaviour-based (Cell, Zone — live on GameObjects) or plain classes (CellData, CommuneData, TerritoryData — for serialization/save)
- **Grid**: 2D isometric with height system (heightMap). Cells stored in `Cell[,] cellArray` and `GameObject[,] gridArray`
- **Sorting order**: complex system determining draw order based on Y position + height
- **Reference file for best practices**: `EconomyManager.cs` (XML docs + #regions + [Header] attributes)
